{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:55:50.539Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing Repository Layers**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the repository layers. I plan to create `users.py`, `clients.py`, and `portal_items.py` repositories. The immediate task is the design of `backend/app/repositories/users.py`.\n\n\n**Defining User Interface**\n\nI've outlined the necessary user service/auth service operations, including `get_user_by_email`, `create_user`, and `authenticate_user`. Now, I'm defining the user attributes in DynamoDB, like `email`, `hashed_password`, `full_name`, `role`, `client_id`, and `is_active`. I'm exploring Python object structures; wrapping them in a class or custom objects ensures both dictionary and attribute-like access. I'll create a lightweight `User` class for this.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T20:55:50.542Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"hadh4bh9","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/app/repositories/users.py","new_text":"import datetime\nfrom typing import Optional, List\nfrom ..core.config import settings\nfrom .dynamodb_client import db_manager\n\nclass DynamoUser:\n    def __init__(self, data: dict):\n        self.email = data.get(\"email\")\n        self.hashed_password = data.get(\"hashed_password\")\n        self.full_name = data.get(\"full_name\") or data.get(\"name\")\n        self.name = self.full_name\n        self.role = data.get(\"role\")\n        self.client_id = data.get(\"client_id\")\n        # Ensure client_id is convertible to string/int for compatibility\n        if self.client_id is not None:\n            self.client_id = str(self.client_id)\n        self.is_active = data.get(\"is_active\", True)\n        self.created_at = data.get(\"created_at\") or datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()\n        \n    def to_dict(self):\n        return {\n            \"email\": self.email,\n            \"hashed_password\": self.hashed_password,\n            \"full_name\": self.full_name,\n            \"name\": self.name,\n            \"role\": self.role,\n            \"client_id\": self.client_id,\n            \"is_active\": self.is_active,\n            \"created_at\": self.created_at\n        }\n\nclass UsersRepository:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.table = db_manager.get_table(settings.DYNAMODB_USERS_TABLE)\n\n    def get_by_email(self, email: str) -> Optional[DynamoUser]:\n        try:\n            res = self.table.get_item(Key={\"email\": email})\n            item = res.get(\"Item\")\n            if item:\n                return DynamoUser(item)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        return None\n\n    def create(self, user_data: dict) -> DynamoUser:\n        user = DynamoUser(user_data)\n        self.table.put_item(Item=user.to_dict())\n        return user\n\n    def update(self, email: str, update_data: dict) -> Optional[DynamoUser]:\n        user = self.get_by_email(email)\n        if not user:\n            return None\n        data = user.to_dict()\n        data.update(update_data)\n        updated = DynamoUser(data)\n        self.table.put_item(Item=updated.to_dict())\n        return updated\n\n    def delete(self, email: str) -> bool:\n        user = self.get_by_email(email)\n        if not user:\n            return False\n        self.table.delete_item(Key={\"email\": email})\n        return True\n\n    def list_users(self) -> List[DynamoUser]:\n        res = self.table.scan()\n        return [DynamoUser(item) for item in res.get(\"Items\", [])]\n\nusers_repo = UsersRepository()\n"}}}
