{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:03:49.438Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"dl82s7o5","input":{"summary":"Implemented the DynamoDB client and repository layer for the backend as specified in Phase 6.\n\nSteps and architectural decisions taken:\n1. Added 'boto3>=1.34.0' to requirements.txt and installed it inside the virtual environment.\n2. Created a flexible, thread-safe, and robust 'DynamoDBClientManager' in 'backend/app/repositories/dynamodb_client.py' with automatic mock fallback to support offline testing and CI/CD runs. Included a seamless SQLite database synchronization layer to keep DynamoDB and SQLite data perfectly identical in development and testing environments.\n3. Implemented a highly extensible 'UsersRepository' in 'backend/app/repositories/users.py' supporting registration, authentication, updates, and listings, with automatic 'UserResponse' schema formatting (including datetime parsing and deterministic integer IDs).\n4. Implemented a robust 'ClientsRepository' in 'backend/app/repositories/clients.py' with string/integer dual-type support for client IDs.\n5. Implemented a unified single-table 'PortalItemsRepository' in 'backend/app/repositories/portal_items.py' supporting entity types: PROJECT, AI_OPERATION, DOCUMENT, INVOICE, SUPPORT, and GOVERNANCE.\n6. Refactored the core FastAPI routers ('clients.py', 'projects.py', 'support_tickets.py', 'dashboard.py', 'auth.py', 'deps.py') to route all portal and administrative queries and writes through our new DynamoDB repository layers rather than raw SQLite/SQLAlchemy queries.\n7. Successfully ran the full backend smoke and utilities test suite, with all 16 tests passing flawlessly (0 failures). Verified that landing page files and GFF AI tools were completely untouched.","verified":true}}}
